Tragedy struck in Igede Ekiti, headquarters of Irepodun, Ifelodun local government area of Ekiti State, as a council worker, Mrs Tayo Ajayi was hacked to death in her room. The incident, it was gathered, occurred last Friday in the residence of the  deceased located within Ujumu compound, Odo Igede quarters, Igede Ekiti. According to the residents, Mrs Ajayi, who was a staff of the Primary Health Centre Department of the local government, was seen on Thursday evening preceding the night she was said to have been murdered. The killing has caused panic among the residents of the town, particularly, the Onigede-in- council, while the corpse had been deposited at the morgue of General Hospital, Igede Ekiti. The deceased’s first son, Toyin Ajayi who spoke on the incident said her mother was killed inside her room, which suggested that she must have been trailed to her home and attacked in the midnight. “I received a call as regard the death of my mother and on getting there, I met my mother in a pool of blood in her room with bruises on her head and blood all over her body indicating that she was macheted to death”.